ATM Backend Console Application (Java, OOPS)

A simple console-based ATM backend simulation written in Java, demonstrating core OOP concepts such as interfaces, inheritance, method overriding, and encapsulation. The app simulates typical ATM flows: card insertion, language selection, PIN verification, withdraw, deposit, balance check, and PIN reset with OTP.

